  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. The model is intended to identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. A full 13-factor assessment is documented: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The intended use scope — predicting normalized index of hemolysis across the CPB operating envelope (flow 2–8 L/min, head 60–120 mmHg, rotor speed 1500–3500 RPM) — is described in the bound requirement and claim records. This package conforms to the Minimal profile; structured Context-of-Use linkage is not required under this profile.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/morrison/req/cpb-hemolysis-mrl2",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/morrison/claim/cpb-hemolysis-worst-case",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/morrison/model/cfd-hemolysis-v3",
